                           WILD INDONESIA-MAGICAL FORESTS
                          --------------------------------


Magical Forests enters the steamy jungles of Borneo, Sumatra and Java, where highly endangered Asian elephants and hairy rhinos still roam.

Thousands of miles to the east, we visit the New Guinea jungle, to find a spiny echidna, prowling the forest floor whilst the little known tree-house people live in fragile homes perched precariously in the highest branches. From sluggish tree kangaroos to flying foxes, Indonesia is a unique meeting point for wildlife from the East and West.



Narrated by:  John Lynch
